icities, the tidal interaction becomes too\nstrong, so the high observed eccentricities cannot be reproduced. However, even\nif we assume tides to be ineffective, the eccentricities in our models do not\nexceed $\\approx 0.25$. We conclude that either our knowledge of disc-binary\ninteractions is still incomplete, or the binaries must have left their phase of\nstrong interaction in an eccentric orbit.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 18 Aug 2020 18:00:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-10-28"}
