{18}-1.6 \\times 10^{19}$ kg in total). About half of the accreted\nimpactor's materials are vaporized, and the rest is completely melted upon the\nimpact. We expect that the further interplay between our theoretical results\nand forthcoming surface observations of Mercury, including the BepiColombo\nmission, will lead us to a better understanding of Mercury's origin and\nevolution.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 19 Aug 2020 15:06:10 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-10-07"}
